'''Socioecology''' is the scientific study of how social structure and organization are influenced by an organism's environment. Socioecology is primarily related to [[anthropology]], [[geography]], [[sociology]], and [[ecology]]. Specifically, the term is used in [[human ecology]], the study of the interaction between humans and their [[habitat|environment]].

